description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Senior Human Resources Advisor (Band 6) to join our Trust, supporting our HR Operations business continuity and COVID-19 related activity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust’s values and commitment to our diversity and inclusion agenda are part of what helps us to retain our CQC rating of ‘Outstanding’ for our patients and service users. Our agenda has become more important than ever, with COVID-19 highlighting some of the social injustices and inequalities within the NHS. If you are interested in joining us on this continuing journey, we’d like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful, you will be an integral part of enabling the NHS People Plan activities to continue whilst supporting COVID-19. This includes risk assessment completion assurance, updating COVID-19 Workforce hub resources and Frequently Asked Questions, COVID-19 advice. A key aspect of the role is to lead on the development of the HR Operations intranet offer and e-learning packages to support the Trust’s commitment to build line management capability, improving people practices and a Restorative Just Culture. This is fundamental; as part achieving our People Strategy promises focused on an Inclusive Culture and Health and Wellbeing, which are aligned to the NHS People Plan as part of Looking after our people and Belonging in the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to these specific work packages, you will be involved in the provision of HR generalist advice and casework across our people lifecycle, including recruitment, Agenda for Change sickness absence, disciplinary, grievance, capability / performance management, management of change and policy reviews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a degree in HR or equivalent experience and have achieved or are working towards Chartered membership of the CIPD, we are interested in hearing from you. The successful candidate will have knowledge of employment law, NHS terms and conditions, including Agenda for Change, experience of working with Trade Unions and handling complex employee relations issues and will be used to working with a diverse range of stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requirement is full-time and available on a fixed term basis until 31st March 2021. Interested applicants will be asked to work flexibly and in an agile way, including, currently working from home for the majority of time in light of the current COVID-19 circumstances and Government guidance. Secondments and part-time applications may be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested? If so, we look forward to receiving your application soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSarah VincentEmail addresssarah.vincent@combined.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
